 679 @tf_export('linalg.cholesky', 'cholesky')
 680 @deprecated_endpoints('cholesky')
 681 def cholesky(input, name=None):
 682   r"""Computes the Cholesky decomposition of one or more square matrices.
 683 
 684   The input is a tensor of shape `[..., M, M]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
 685   form square matrices.
 686 
 687   The input has to be symmetric and positive definite. Only the lower-triangular
 688   part of the input will be used for this operation. The upper-triangular part
 689   will not be read.
 690 
 691   The output is a tensor of the same shape as the input
 692   containing the Cholesky decompositions for all input submatrices `[..., :, :]`.
 693 
 694   **Note**: The gradient computation on GPU is faster for large matrices but
 695   not for large batch dimensions when the submatrices are small. In this
 696   case it might be faster to use the CPU.
 697 
 698   Args:
 699     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
 700       Shape is `[..., M, M]`.
 701     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 702 
 703   Returns:
 704     A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
 705   """

 708     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 709         "Cholesky", input=input, name=name)

 714       "Cholesky", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 715     _result, = _result
 716     return _result
 717 
 718   else:
 719     try:

 751 def cholesky_grad(l, grad, name=None):
 752   r"""Computes the reverse mode backpropagated gradient of the Cholesky algorithm.
 753

 756 
 757   Args:
 758     l: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float32`, `float64`.
 759       Output of batch Cholesky algorithm l = cholesky(A). Shape is `[..., M, M]`.
 760       Algorithm depends only on lower triangular part of the innermost matrices of
 761       this tensor.
 762     grad: A `Tensor`. Must have the same type as `l`.
 763       df/dl where f is some scalar function. Shape is `[..., M, M]`.
 764       Algorithm depends only on lower triangular part of the innermost matrices of
 765       this tensor.

 822 def log_matrix_determinant(input, name=None):
 823   r"""Computes the sign and the log of the absolute value of the determinant of
 824 
 825   one or more square matrices.
 826 
 827   The input is a tensor of shape `[N, M, M]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
 828   form square matrices. The outputs are two tensors containing the signs and
 829   absolute values of the log determinants for all N input submatrices
 830   `[..., :, :]` such that the determinant = sign*exp(log_abs_determinant).
 831   The log_abs_determinant is computed as det(P)*sum(log(diag(LU))) where LU
 832   is the LU decomposition of the input and P is the corresponding
 833   permutation matrix.
 834 
 835   Args:
 836     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float32`, `float64`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
 837       Shape is `[N, M, M]`.
 838     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 839 
 840   Returns:
 841     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (sign, log_abs_determinant).
 842 
 843     sign: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
 844     log_abs_determinant: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
 845   """
 846   _ctx = _context._context
 847   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 848     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 849         "LogMatrixDeterminant", input=input, name=name)
 850     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 851     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 852     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"))
 853     _execute.record_gradient(
 854       "LogMatrixDeterminant", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 855     _result = _LogMatrixDeterminantOutput._make(_result)
 856     return _result

 861         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
 862         "LogMatrixDeterminant", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, input)
 863       _result = _LogMatrixDeterminantOutput._make(_result)
 864       return _result
 865     except _core._FallbackException:
 866       return log_matrix_determinant_eager_fallback(
 867           input, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
 868     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:

1009 @tf_export('linalg.inv', 'matrix_inverse')
1010 @deprecated_endpoints('matrix_inverse')
1011 def matrix_inverse(input, adjoint=False, name=None):
1012   r"""Computes the inverse of one or more square invertible matrices or their
1013 
1014   adjoints (conjugate transposes).
1015 
1016   The input is a tensor of shape `[..., M, M]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
1017   form square matrices. The output is a tensor of the same shape as the input
1018   containing the inverse for all input submatrices `[..., :, :]`.
1019 
1020   The op uses LU decomposition with partial pivoting to compute the inverses.
1021 
1022   If a matrix is not invertible there is no guarantee what the op does. It
1023   may detect the condition and raise an exception or it may simply return a
1024   garbage result.
1025 
1026   Args:
1027     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
1028       Shape is `[..., M, M]`.
1029     adjoint: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
1030     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1031 
1032   Returns:
1033     A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1034   """
1035   _ctx = _context._context
1036   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1037     if adjoint is None:
1038       adjoint = False
1039     adjoint = _execute.make_bool(adjoint, "adjoint")
1040     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1041         "MatrixInverse", input=input, adjoint=adjoint, name=name)
1042     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1043     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1044     _attrs = ("adjoint", _op.get_attr("adjoint"), "T", _op.get_attr("T"))
1045     _execute.record_gradient(
1046       "MatrixInverse", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1047     _result, = _result
1048     return _result
1049 
1050   else:
1051     try:
1052       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1053         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1054         "MatrixInverse", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, input,

1087 def matrix_logarithm(input, name=None):
1088   r"""Computes the matrix logarithm of one or more square matrices:
1089 
1090   
1091   \\(log(exp(A)) = A\\)
1092 
1093   This op is only defined for complex matrices. If A is positive-definite and
1094   real, then casting to a complex matrix, taking the logarithm and casting back
1095   to a real matrix will give the correct result.
1096 
1097   This function computes the matrix logarithm using the Schur-Parlett algorithm.
1098   Details of the algorithm can be found in Section 11.6.2 of:
1099   Nicholas J. Higham, Functions of Matrices: Theory and Computation, SIAM 2008.
1100   ISBN 978-0-898716-46-7.
1101 
1102   The input is a tensor of shape `[..., M, M]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
1103   form square matrices. The output is a tensor of the same shape as the input
1104   containing the exponential for all input submatrices `[..., :, :]`.
1105 
1106   Args:
1107     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `complex64`, `complex128`.
1108       Shape is `[..., M, M]`.

1236 def matrix_solve_ls(matrix, rhs, l2_regularizer, fast=True, name=None):
1237   r"""Solves one or more linear least-squares problems.
1238 
1239   `matrix` is a tensor of shape `[..., M, N]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
1240   form real or complex matrices of size `[M, N]`. `Rhs` is a tensor of the same
1241   type as `matrix` and shape `[..., M, K]`.
1242   The output is a tensor shape `[..., N, K]` where each output matrix solves
1243   each of the equations
1244   `matrix[..., :, :]` * `output[..., :, :]` = `rhs[..., :, :]`
1245   in the least squares sense.
1246 
1247   We use the following notation for (complex) matrix and right-hand sides
1248   in the batch:
1249 
1250   `matrix`=\\(A \in \mathbb{C}^{m \times n}\\),
1251   `rhs`=\\(B  \in \mathbb{C}^{m \times k}\\),
1252   `output`=\\(X  \in \mathbb{C}^{n \times k}\\),
1253   `l2_regularizer`=\\(\lambda \in \mathbb{R}\\).
1254 
1255   If `fast` is `True`, then the solution is computed by solving the normal
1256   equations using Cholesky decomposition. Specifically, if \\(m \ge n\\) then
1257   \\(X = (A^H A + \lambda I)^{-1} A^H B\\), which solves the least-squares
1258   problem \\(X = \mathrm{argmin}_{Z \in \Re^{n \times k} } ||A Z - B||_F^2 + \lambda ||Z||_F^2\\). 
1259   If \\(m \lt n\\) then `output` is computed as
1260   \\(X = A^H (A A^H + \lambda I)^{-1} B\\), which (for \\(\lambda = 0\\)) is the
1261   minimum-norm solution to the under-determined linear system, i.e.
1262   \\(X = \mathrm{argmin}_{Z \in \mathbb{C}^{n \times k} } ||Z||_F^2 \\),
1263   subject to \\(A Z = B\\). Notice that the fast path is only numerically stable
1264   when \\(A\\) is numerically full rank and has a condition number
1265   \\(\mathrm{cond}(A) \lt \frac{1}{\sqrt{\epsilon_{mach} } }\\) or \\(\lambda\\) is
1266   sufficiently large.
1267 
1268   If `fast` is `False` an algorithm based on the numerically robust complete
1269   orthogonal decomposition is used. This computes the minimum-norm
1270   least-squares solution, even when \\(A\\) is rank deficient. This path is
1271   typically 6-7 times slower than the fast path. If `fast` is `False` then
1272   `l2_regularizer` is ignored.
1273 
1274   Args:
1275     matrix: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
1276       Shape is `[..., M, N]`.
1277     rhs: A `Tensor`. Must have the same type as `matrix`.
1278       Shape is `[..., M, K]`.
1279     l2_regularizer: A `Tensor` of type `float64`. Scalar tensor.
1280 
1281       @compatibility(numpy)
1282       Equivalent to np.linalg.lstsq
1283       @end_compatibility
1284     fast: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
1285     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1286 
1287   Returns:
1288     A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `matrix`.
1289   """
1290   _ctx = _context._context
1291   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1292     if fast is None:
1293       fast = True
1294     fast = _execute.make_bool(fast, "fast")
1295     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1296         "MatrixSolveLs", matrix=matrix, rhs=rhs,
1297         l2_regularizer=l2_regularizer, fast=fast, name=name)
1298     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1299     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1300     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"), "fast", _op.get_attr("fast"))
1301     _execute.record_gradient(
1302       "MatrixSolveLs", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1303     _result, = _result
1304     return _result
1305 
1306   else:
1307     try:
1308       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1309         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1310         "MatrixSolveLs", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, matrix, rhs,
1311         l2_regularizer, "fast", fast)
1312       return _result
1313     except _core._FallbackException:
1314       return matrix_solve_ls_eager_fallback(
1315           matrix, rhs, l2_regularizer, fast=fast, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1316     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1317       if name is not None:
1318         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1319       else:
1320         message = e.message
1321       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
1322

1325   r"""This is the slowpath function for Eager mode.
1326   This is for function matrix_solve_ls

1493               _op.get_attr("T"))

1536 def self_adjoint_eig(input, name=None):
1537   r"""Computes the Eigen Decomposition of a batch of square self-adjoint matrices.
1538

1540   form square matrices, with the same constraints as the single matrix

1544   eigenvalues, and subsequent [...,1:, :] containing the eigenvectors. The eigenvalues
1545   are sorted in non-decreasing order.
1546 
1547   Args:
1548     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`.
1549       Shape is `[..., M, M]`.
1550     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1551 
1552   Returns:
1553     A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1554   """
1555   _ctx = _context._context
1556   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1557     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1558         "SelfAdjointEig", input=input, name=name)
1559     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1560     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1561     _attrs = ("T", _op.get_attr("T"))
1562     _execute.record_gradient(
1563       "SelfAdjointEig", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1564     _result, = _result
1565     return _result
1566

1605 def self_adjoint_eig_v2(input, compute_v=True, name=None):
1606   r"""Computes the eigen decomposition of one or more square self-adjoint matrices.
1607 
1608   Computes the eigenvalues and (optionally) eigenvectors of each inner matrix in
1609   `input` such that `input[..., :, :] = v[..., :, :] * diag(e[..., :])`. The eigenvalues
1610   are sorted in non-decreasing order.
1611 
1612   ```python
1613   # a is a tensor.
1614   # e is a tensor of eigenvalues.
1615   # v is a tensor of eigenvectors.
1616   e, v = self_adjoint_eig(a)
1617   e = self_adjoint_eig(a, compute_v=False)
1618   ```
1619 
1620   Args:
1621     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
1622       `Tensor` input of shape `[N, N]`.
1623     compute_v: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
1624       If `True` then eigenvectors will be computed and returned in `v`.
1625       Otherwise, only the eigenvalues will be computed.
1626     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1627 
1628   Returns:
1629     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (e, v).
1630 
1631     e: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1632     v: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1633   """
1634   _ctx = _context._context
1635   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1636     if compute_v is None:
1637       compute_v = True
1638     compute_v = _execute.make_bool(compute_v, "compute_v")
1639     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1640         "SelfAdjointEigV2", input=input, compute_v=compute_v, name=name)
1641     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1642     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1643     _attrs = ("compute_v", _op.get_attr("compute_v"), "T", _op.get_attr("T"))
1644     _execute.record_gradient(
1645       "SelfAdjointEigV2", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1646     _result = _SelfAdjointEigV2Output._make(_result)
1647     return _result
1648 
1649   else:
1650     try:
1651       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1652         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1653         "SelfAdjointEigV2", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, input,
1654         "compute_v", compute_v)
1655       _result = _SelfAdjointEigV2Output._make(_result)
1656       return _result
1657     except _core._FallbackException:
1658       return self_adjoint_eig_v2_eager_fallback(
1659           input, compute_v=compute_v, name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1660     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1661       if name is not None:
1662         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1663       else:
1664         message = e.message
1665       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

1692 def svd(input, compute_uv=True, full_matrices=False, name=None):
1693   r"""Computes the singular value decompositions of one or more matrices.
1694 
1695   Computes the SVD of each inner matrix in `input` such that
1696   `input[..., :, :] = u[..., :, :] * diag(s[..., :, :]) * transpose(v[..., :, :])`
1697 
1698   ```python
1699   # a is a tensor containing a batch of matrices.
1700   # s is a tensor of singular values for each matrix.
1701   # u is the tensor containing of left singular vectors for each matrix.
1702   # v is the tensor containing of right singular vectors for each matrix.
1703   s, u, v = svd(a)
1704   s, _, _ = svd(a, compute_uv=False)
1705   ```
1706 
1707   Args:
1708     input: A `Tensor`. Must be one of the following types: `float64`, `float32`, `complex64`, `complex128`.
1709       A tensor of shape `[..., M, N]` whose inner-most 2 dimensions
1710       form matrices of size `[M, N]`. Let `P` be the minimum of `M` and `N`.
1711     compute_uv: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `True`.
1712       If true, left and right singular vectors will be
1713       computed and returned in `u` and `v`, respectively.
1714       If false, `u` and `v` are not set and should never referenced.
1715     full_matrices: An optional `bool`. Defaults to `False`.
1716       If true, compute full-sized `u` and `v`. If false
1717       (the default), compute only the leading `P` singular vectors.
1718       Ignored if `compute_uv` is `False`.
1719     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1720 
1721   Returns:
1722     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (s, u, v).
1723 
1724     s: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1725     u: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1726     v: A `Tensor`. Has the same type as `input`.
1727   """
1728   _ctx = _context._context
1729   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
1730     if compute_uv is None:
1731       compute_uv = True
1732     compute_uv = _execute.make_bool(compute_uv, "compute_uv")
1733     if full_matrices is None:
1734       full_matrices = False
1735     full_matrices = _execute.make_bool(full_matrices, "full_matrices")
1736     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1737         "Svd", input=input, compute_uv=compute_uv,
1738         full_matrices=full_matrices, name=name)
1739     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1740     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1741     _attrs = ("compute_uv", _op.get_attr("compute_uv"), "full_matrices",
1742               _op.get_attr("full_matrices"), "T", _op.get_attr("T"))
1743     _execute.record_gradient(
1744       "Svd", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1745     _result = _SvdOutput._make(_result)
1746     return _result
1747 
1748   else:
1749     try:
1750       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1751         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name, "Svd", name,
1752         _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, input, "compute_uv", compute_uv,
1753         "full_matrices", full_matrices)
1754       _result = _SvdOutput._make(_result)
1755       return _result
1756     except _core._FallbackException:
1757       return svd_eager_fallback(
1758           input, compute_uv=compute_uv, full_matrices=full_matrices,
1759           name=name, ctx=_ctx)
1760     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1761       if name is not None:
1762         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1763       else:
1764         message = e.message
1765       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)
